      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Covenant for the restoration of the Insignia of a Companion of The Most Distinguished Order of Saint Michael and Saint George. ¶ The text of the covenant, in an unknown hand, was sent to M as an enclo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.07.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Gordon Gairdner</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">National Archives, London, CO<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>447/11, Order of St Michael and St. George, 1869, Individuals, 10048.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Covenant for the restoration of the Insignia of a Companion of The Most Distinguished Order of Saint Michael and Saint George.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text of the covenant, in an unknown hand, was sent to M as an enclosure to G. Gairdner to M, 26 April 1869. M inserted: 'Melbourne, Colony of Victoria', and 'tenth' and 'July', signed the form and added his qualifications. Rudall signed his name and added his qualifications.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The form<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was returned, through the Governor of Victoria, as an enclosure to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to G. Gairdner, 13 July 1869<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 69-07-13c).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I hereby Covenant and promise, that in case I should hereafter be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>promoted, or cease to hold my rank<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and place in this Most distinguished Order, I will forthwith restore to the Secretary and Registrar all the Insignia thereof which I have now received from the Sovereign, or from the said Secretary and Registrar; and I further promise that I will, without delay, make provision for the due Restoration of the said Insignia by my Personal Representatives, in case I shall continue a Member of this Order until the Period of my decease.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">badge was</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>returned upon M's promotion to Knight Commander in the Order; see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">M t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">o R. Herbert, 29 September 1879</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">in this edition as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">79-09-29b</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Given under my hand at<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne, Colony of Victoria, this tenth day of July 1869</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ph.D., M.D., F.R.S.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Witness</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">James T. Rudall</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Fellow of the Royal College</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">of Surgeons of England.</p>
